summary: I still find this so funny. David Tennant, and Russell T. Davies, were wild. They announced they were leaving the show, did...
body: I still find this so funny. David Tennant, and Russell T. Davies, were wild. They announced they were leaving the show, did their last full season as Doctor and showrunner, then proceeded to do like an additional YEAR of specials. They really dragged it out lol. Which would make David still the longest running New Who Doctor, wouldn’t it? Only 3 actual seasons like Peter and Matt did, but a total of 5 years as the Doctor.

summary:
Behind the scenes of The Sound of Drums/The Last of the Time Lords (Part Eight) 

  Excerpt from Doctor Who Magazine #385 -...
caption:
Behind the scenes of The Sound of Drums/The Last of the Time Lords
(Part Eight)

Excerpt from Doctor Who Magazine #385 - article by Benjamin Cook:

[filming in a very cold slate quarry]
The Master, John Simm, is coping more admirably with the sub-zero (well, almost sub-zero) conditions.  He’s standing atop a mound of what’s almost certainly slate, striking poses for on-set visual effects supervisor Barney Curnow, who’s recording them for posterity’s sake on a digital camera.  “Comedy pose?” offers John.

“Best not,” chips in David Tennant, “It’s gonna be made eventually.”

Indeed, these snapshots are so that Barney and his colleagues at The Mill can create a CGI statue of the Master. Possibly doing a Basil Fawlty Nazi salute, at this rate. Or a classic Bruce Forsythe pose. “Or how about just a fig leaf?” offers John.

Barney opens his mouth as if to say, “Enough with the comedy poses already,” but snaps it shut again as John straightens up and postures, as the Master might, with arms folded and a steely glare. “Now, that’s more like it,” grins the man from The Mill.

Thank you to everyone who shared set photos!

Previous parts are available here: [one] [two] [three] [four] [five] [six] [seven]
Other behind-the-scenes photosets are available here

summary: River was so confused as to why the doctor was acting as if he hadn't a clue of who she was, so whilst everyone else got to work...
body:
River was so confused as to why the doctor was acting as if he hadn’t a clue of who she was, so whilst everyone else got to work and herself and the doctor sat down in a corner of the libary, she decided to take this chance to go through thir diary.

“Thanks.” River said an slight hurry as she grabbed her diary from her bag

“For what?” The doctor frowned, unsure as to what exactly he’d done for thi strange woman to thank him.

“The usual, for coming when I call.”

“Oh that was you?”

“You’re doing a very good job, acting like you don’t know me. I assume there’s a reason.” River sighed as she flicked through her diary trying to find a place to start

“A fairly good one, actually.” The doctor replied trying not to be too sarcastic in his tone, he hadn’t a clue who she was, so why did she think they knew one another?

“Okay, shall we do diaries then? Where are we this time? Going by your face, I’d say it’s early days for you, yeah? So, erm…Crash of the Byzantium…have we done that yet?” River asked with a hopefulness in her eye

However the doctor just looked back with a blank experssion cover his face

“Obviously ringing no bells…Right, picnic at asgard. Have we done asgard yet?” River asked, excitement filling her, just thinking about all the memories they shared at asgard.

When the doctor didn’t answer but still had that same blank experssion covering his face, River just raised a slightly worried eyebrow at him “Obvioulsy not. Blimey very early dys, then. Hoo! Life with a time traveller - never knew it could be such hard work.” River chuckled

She flicked through a couple pages, before she looked up at the doctor, the person she loved more than anyone else in the world, but how early was this for the doctor.

“Look at you! You’re young.” River gasped

“I’m really not you know.” The doctor said with a laugh, he was 900 years old, he was the furthest thing from young.

“Your eyes.” River beamed, as she placed a hand on the side of the doctors face, he was so young “You’re younger than I’ve ever seen you.” River said stroking the side of his face gently.

“You’ve seen me before, then?” The doctor frowned

Those words, she’d hoped she was wrong, she hoped he didn’t mean it “Doctor…please tell me you know who I am?”

The doctor looked down at the blue tardis diary and looked back up at River “Who are you?”

River slowly took her hand away from the doctor and to her own lap, those words, they just broke her, the killed her inside. She always knew this day would come, but it was too soon, she wasn’t ready for the doctor to not even know who she was. her own husband, her love, he didn’t know who she was and it killed her inside, because she knew who he was and she loved him with every piece of her soul. oh did she love him.

But the fact that he didn’t know her, it tore her apart, it broke her heart.

Then she knew. This time. This is where she came to die.
